x,y
\lVert x+y\rVert = \lVert x\rVert + \lVert y\rVert
u,v
\lVert u+v\rVert = 2
\lVert x\rVert + \lVert y\rVert = 2
\lVert x\rVert = \lVert y\rVert
1-\eta = \lVert x\rVert < \lVert y\rVert = 1+\eta
v = \frac{1}{1+\eta}y
u = x + \frac{\eta}{1+\eta}y
u
v
u+v = x+y
\lVert u+v\rVert = 2
\lVert v\rVert = \frac{1}{1+\eta}\lVert y\rVert = 1
\lVert u\rVert = \left\lVert x + \frac{\eta}{1+\eta}y\right\rVert \leqslant \lVert x\rVert + \frac{\eta}{1+\eta}\lVert y\rVert = (1-\eta) + \eta = 1,
\lVert u\rVert \geqslant \lVert u+v\rVert - \lVert v\rVert = 2-1=1
\lVert u\rVert = 1
2 =||x+y|| = \langle x + y, x +y \rangle = ||x||^2 + 2Re\langle x, y \rangle + ||y||^2 = 2 + 2Re\langle x, y \rangle \implies Re\langle x,y  \rangle = \langle x, y \rangle = 0
\langle x, y \rangle = ||x|| ||y|| \cos \theta
\cos \theta = 0 \implies x,y 
